Why Greatest Hits, Vol. 1 is the better fit:
- Concise, front‑to‑back single‑disc compilation with careful sequencing directly matches my preference for song‑forward sequencing and consistent dynamics suitable for whole‑disc listening rather than an inconsistent anthology.
- The description emphasizes punchy midrange, subtle dynamics and “human‑in‑the‑room” production while also noting clear instrument separation and song‑serving solos. That suggests preserved transient snap and punch (important for tight bass/drums and guitar attack) rather than the murky/warmed‑out mastering I dislike.
